**Damage Report:**

**Vehicle Description:** The image shows a close-up view of a vehicle's side panel, specifically focusing on the area near the rear wheel well.

**Location of Damage:** The damage appears to be located on the lower portion of the vehicle's side panel, just above the wheel well. It is situated along the chrome trim line that runs horizontally across the vehicle's body.

**Type of Damage:** The damage consists of a noticeable scratch or dent. The surface of the paint has been disturbed, creating a visible indentation. The scratch appears to be linear and extends horizontally across the panel. There is also some minor chipping of the paint around the edges of the scratch, indicating that the impact was not purely cosmetic but caused some physical damage to the vehicle's body.

**Conclusion:** The vehicle has sustained physical damage in the form of a scratch/dent on its side panel. This damage requires attention and repair to restore the vehicle's appearance and structural integrity.

**Recommendation:** It is advisable to have a professional inspection by a qualified mechanic or body shop to assess the extent of the damage and determine the appropriate course of action for repair.
